@@ -57,3 +57,9 @@ The gate does not certify devotional scholarship, production interaction quality
 ## Release 234 route-registry gate
 
 The governance workflow regenerates the canonical override registry from the audited boundary fixture and fails on semantic or byte-level drift. The historical `data/site-routes.json` snapshot remains unchanged.
+
+## Release 235 repository hygiene gate
+
+Tracked compiler caches, bytecode, temporary extraction directories, validation artefacts and build outputs are prohibited. The governance workflow runs with `PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE=1`, validates tracked paths before release attestation and uploads a separate hygiene report.
+
+The Release 235 cleanup removes thirteen accidentally tracked Python cache files. Full rollback uses `git revert`; the implementation patch intentionally does not recreate generated bytecode.
